ul.li:
Language - allows
        you to localize the interface and change the language to English, French, German, Dutch,
        Japanese, or Italian. Restart the application to apply the current selection;

Line separator -
        this option defines the line separator. The System Default choice
        sets the platform-specific line separator;

Default Internet browser - the path to a web browser of choice, used for:
opening (X)HTML or PDF transformation results;
opening a web page (for example, pointing to specific paragraphs in the W3C recommendation of XML Schema in case of XML Schema validation errors).

Open last edited files from
          project - when enabled,  opens the last edited
        files from project at start-up;

Last visited directory - when
        selected, the Open file dialog memorizes
        the last visited folder. When used next time, it starts directly in this folder;

Directory of the edited file -
        the Open file
          dialog starts in the folder where the currently edited file is stored;
